name: Adnama
content:
Adnama was a resident of Galactic City on Coruscant during the years leading up to the Clone Wars. She was known to have visited the Outlander Club in the Uscru Entertainment District, and was there on the night that Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker pursued the assassin Zam Wesell into the club.
Adnama was portrayed by Amanda Lucas, daughter of director George Lucas, in Attack of the Clones. The name "Adnama" is "Amanda" spelled backwards. Amanda also provided the voice of Tey How and portrayed Diva Funquita in The Phantom Menace, and portrayed Senator Terr Taneel in Revenge of the Sith.
